modules.description: Provides functions for capturing and injecting raw Ethernet frames, with support for BPF and AF_PACKET backends. Operates on byte sequences and Ethernet headers, enabling low-level network manipulation. Used for tasks like crafting custom Ethernet packets, implementing network monitoring tools, or bypassing higher-level protocol stacks.

Provides functions to open, read from, and write to raw network interfaces, supporting packet filtering with BPF or AF_SOCKET. Operates on network interfaces and Cstruct.t buffers to handle full Ethernet frames. Used for capturing DHCP traffic by applying specific BPF filters for server and client ports.
